# Experiment No.4: 

The aim of this experiment is to implement **interface** in Java by defining and implementing an interface that 
demonstrates polymorphism.

A. Write a program to implement an interface. 
B. Write a Java program to demonstrate extended interface.

interface Animal {
    void makeSound();
}

class Dog implements Animal {
    public void makeSound() {
        System.out.println("Dog barks");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Animal a = new Dog();
        a.makeSound(); // Output: Dog barks
    }
}



interface A {
    void showA();
}

interface B extends A {
    void showB();
}

class Demo implements B {
    public void showA() {
        System.out.println("Inside showA()");
    }

    public void showB() {
        System.out.println("Inside showB()");
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Demo  d = new Demo();
        d.showA();
        d.showB();
    }
}
